sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: M13K07 modified, from HpaI to BamHI site
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: modified by Rebecca Adams to separate genes, promoters, and RBS's in order to make refactoring easier.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M13503
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
This RBS is part of the bacteriophage M13 genome, initiating translation of the gene III message (BBa_M13003). The part aligns with base pairs 1563-1578 in M13K07 genome. It was identified as the RBS for gene III message by Wezenbeek et al in Gene (1980) 11: 129-148
New England Biolabs M13K07. Sequenced in 2002 by L. Panganaban
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Natalie Kuldell
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: New England Biolabs M13K07. Sequenced in 2002 by L. Panganaban

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M13103
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part is from the bacteriophage M13 genome, bp 1500-1547 in M13K07. It directs transcription of M13 gene III (BBa_M13503, BBa_M13003). Its identity as a promoter was described in Gene (1980) 11:129-148 based on -10,-35 homology and fragment of genome able to bind RNAP.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Natalie Kuldell
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: New England Biolabs M13K07. Sequenced in 2002 by L. Panganaban.
